data.name: Mess in the Bank
data.description:
Peter came to Awesome Bank, because he wants to take out a loan for a car. All required documents were created with 2 (or sometimes more) copies, but gust of wind make a huge mess in documents. You need to help Peter to find copies of documents.

You will receive an array of strings or numbers and you need to find all duplicate documents:
```javascript
solution([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 1]) === [1]
```

All duplicate documents should be provided in order of appearance these duplicates (ignoring the order of original documents). For example:

```javascript
solution([2, 1, 1, 2, 2]); //Should return [1, 2, 2]. Because 2, 1 are original documents and 1, 2, 2 - are copies
solution([3, 2, 1, 1, 2, 4, 3, 2]); //Should return [1, 2, 3, 2]. The order of originals - doesn't matter.
//Documents 3, 2, 1 are originals. And then all documents (skip 4) - are copies: 1, 2, 3, 2 and we should not reorder them.
```

There are millions of documents in the Awesome Bank, so try to be as fast as possible. Also, please, note, that bank is closing in 2 seconds!
